The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Md. Sp. to play opener
                                                   Md. Sp. to play opener
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The Indian Football Association (IFA) announced a revised schedule for the 114th edition of the IFA Shield on Friday, according to which the tournament will be held from August 30 to September 12 at various grounds in and around Calcutta. Mohammedan Sporting play Lajong FC of Meghalaya in the opener.         
	Mohun Bagan and East Bengal will begin their campaign on September 3. While Bagan take on George Telegraph in their first tie, the red-and-gold brigade will face the winners of the Prodyut Dutta Memorial Tournament.         
	The 12 teams have been divided into four groups with the group-toppers moving into the semi-finals. AS Douanes of Senegal are the only foreign team in the meet.         
	The IFA has shortlisted Mohammedan Sporting, Mohun Bagan, East Bengal and Howrah grounds for the league stage of the tournament, IFA secretary Utpal Ganguli revealed.         
	The semi-finals and final will be held on the newly laid artificial turf of the Salt Lake Stadium. We are working out on the detailed fixtures which would be ready by Saturday, Ganguli said. Winners will be richer by Rs 7.5 lakh while the runners-up will take home Rs 5 lakh.         
	The groups         
	Group A: East Bengal, Chirag United SC, winners of Pradyut Dutta Memorial Tournament; Group B: Mohammedan Sporting, Churchill Brothers, Lajong FC; Group C: Mohun Bagan, George Telegraph, Mahindra United; Group D: AS Douanes of Senegal, Air India and Pune FC.                                                                                                                       
